HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1119
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Robert Mason Howard,
2026 Salutatorian at Spring Hill High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Robert Mason Howard is one such exceptional student, who was recently
named Salutatorian of the 2026 graduating class at Spring Hill High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Howard has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Robert Mason Howard has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities,
including National History Day for three years in a row, where he won the regional competition
in 2024 and presented at the State contest; he also completed work-based learning as a
teacher's assistant for Dr. Dodson; and
WHEREAS, his display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well for his
future success as a student at Columbia State Community College, where he will study civil
engineering; and
WHEREAS, Robert Mason Howard's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of
pride for his parents, Michael and Traci Howard, his school, and his community; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Howard's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
HJR1119
014732
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor the 2026 Spring Hill High School
Salutatorian, Robert Mason Howard, on his impressive academic achievement and extend to
him our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
